<article>
    <h1>HON&#xAD;OUR&#xAD;ING THE ELITES OF THE PROP&#xAD;ERTY IN&#xAD;DUS&#xAD;TRY</h1>
    <h2>PropNex Mid Year Con&#xAD;ven&#xAD;tion 2020 cel&#xAD;e&#xAD;brated top in&#xAD;dus&#xAD;try tal&#xAD;ents and of&#xAD;fered in&#xAD;sights to the chang&#xAD;ing real es&#xAD;tate land&#xAD;scape in the cur&#xAD;rent pan&#xAD;demic</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201212/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-12"><time>2020-12-12</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline">This ar&#xAD;ti&#xAD;cle was con&#xAD;trib&#xAD;uted by PropNex.</span>
    </section>

    <p>The spe­cial ‘live’ tele­cast of PropNex Mid Year Con­ven­tion on Septem­ber 16 has gar­nered more than 40,000 views on Face­book to date. The high­light of the event was the sig­na­ture “Con­ver­sa­tion with Min­is­ter” seg­ment fea­tur­ing Guest-of-Hon­our, Mr Desmond Lee, who is Sin­ga­pore’s Min­is­ter for Na­tional Devel­op­ment.</p>
    <p>The en­gag­ing seg­ment show­cased a can­did con­ver­sa­tion be­tween PropNex’s Chief Ex­ec­u­tive Of­fi­cer Is­mail Gafoor and Min­is­ter Desmond Lee about var­i­ous im­por­tant prop­erty top­ics. They in­cluded the re­shap­ing of Sin­ga­pore’s real es­tate sec­tor against the back­drop of the Covid-19 pan­demic, the im­pact of prop­erty cool­ing measures, Gov­ern­ment Land Sites (GLS) and the cur­rent pri­vate hous­ing sup­ply, as well as the fu­ture of HDB flats.</p>
    <p>IM­PACT­ING LIVES WITH $750,000 CON­TRI­BU­TION TO COM­MU­NITY CH­EST</p>
    <p>The event also saw a pre­sen­ta­tion of PropNex’s cheque of $750,000 to the Com­mu­nity Ch­est in the pres­ence of Min­is­ter Desmond Lee and the Chair­man of Com­mu­nity Ch­est, Mr Phillip Tan.</p>
    <p>Mr Is­mail Gafoor said: “We are heart­ened to know that $250,000 goes to help peo­ple af­fected by the Covid-19 sit­u­a­tion, and the front­line heroes who are fighting the virus. PropNex be­gan con­tribut­ing to Com­mu­nity Ch­est in 2013 and we have been donating $500,000 an­nu­ally since 2015 to ben­e­fit the less for­tu­nate and un­der­priv­i­leged chil­dren. We hope this year’s to­tal do­na­tion of $750,000 can touch more lives and ben­e­fit those in need.”</p>
    <p>HON­OUR­ING THE CREAM OF THE CROP</p>
    <p>Dur­ing the event, Min­is­ter Desmond Lee also wit­nessed the cel­e­bra­tion of PropNex’s record num­ber of PropNex Am­bas­sadors. A to­tal of 221 sales­per­sons were cho­sen af­ter go­ing through a rig­or­ous process, which was based on cri­te­ria such as how they mea­sure up in terms of of­fer­ing con­sumer sat­is­fac­tion and main­tain­ing a high level of eth­i­cal con­duct.</p>
    <p>This year is es­pe­cially sig­nif­i­cant as the agency awarded its first batch of 20-Year am­bas­sadors since its in­cep­tion in 2009. The achieve­ments of th­ese out­stand­ing awardees, who have served more than five, 10, 15 or 20 years in PropNex, high­light their pas­sion and com­mit­ment in the real es­tate busi­ness.</p>
    <p>Mr Is­mail Gafoor said: “Truly an iconic ti­tle sought af­ter by PropNex­i­ans, our PropNex Am­bas­sadors are in­deed the hall­mark of ex­cel­lence and rep­re­sen­ta­tives of the real es­tate in­dus­try. This is def­i­nitely a sig­nif­i­cant ac­com­plish­ment for each sales­per­son.”</p>
    <p>Ms Hay­ati Maskuri, a 20-year PropNex Am­bas­sador and sales­per­son, said: “It is an hon­our to be in the first batch of re­cip­i­ents of the 20-Year PropNex Am­bas­sador Award.</p>
    <p>“Be­ing with PropNex since Day One of its in­cep­tion was the start of liv­ing the best years of my life. I have seen how the agency has made tremen­dous growth, not just in build­ing a strong sales­force, but also in the sup­port sys­tems, IT Plat­forms and project op­por­tu­ni­ties for its sales­per­sons. PropNex will def­i­nitely be the first and last agency for me!”</p>
    <p>PropNex be­gan con­tribut­ing to Com­mu­nity Ch­est in 2013 and we have been donating $500,000 an­nu­ally since 2015 to ben­e­fit the less for­tu­nate and un­der­priv­i­leged chil­dren. We hope this year’s to­tal do­na­tion of $750,000 can touch more lives and ben­e­fit those in need.</p>

